---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const mcpUrl = 'https://cocktail.glass/mcp';
const mcpAddCmd = `claude mcp add --transport http cocktail-glass ${mcpUrl}`;

// One-click install deeplinks, built from a single MCP URL source of truth.
const cursorConfig = Buffer.from(JSON.stringify({ url: mcpUrl })).toString('base64');
const cursorInstall = `https://cursor.com/en/install-mcp?name=cocktail-glass&config=${encodeURIComponent(cursorConfig)}`;
const vscodeInstall = `vscode:mcp/install?${encodeURIComponent(
  JSON.stringify({ name: 'cocktail-glass', type: 'http', url: mcpUrl })
)}`;

const desktopConfig = `{
  "mcpServers": {
    "cocktail-glass": {
      "url": "https://cocktail.glass/mcp"
    }
  }
}`;

const exampleRequest = `{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "find_cocktails_by_ingredient",
    "arguments": { "ingredient": "Campari" }
  }
}`;

const exampleResponse = `{
  "count": 29,
  "cocktails": [
    { "name": "Negroni",      "family": "Spirit-Forward", "url": "https://cocktail.glass/negroni/" },
    { "name": "Boulevardier", "family": "Spirit-Forward", "url": "https://cocktail.glass/boulevardier/" },
    { "name": "Jungle Bird",  "family": "Tiki",           "url": "https://cocktail.glass/jungle-bird/" },
    { "name": "Americano",    "family": "Spritz",         "url": "https://cocktail.glass/americano/" }
  ]
}`;

const movieExampleRequest = `{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 2,
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "find_cocktails_in_movie",
    "arguments": { "movie": "The Godfather" }
  }
}`;

const movieExampleResponse = `{
  "count": 6,
  "appearances": [
    { "name": "Godfather",       "movie": "The Godfather",          "year": 1972, "note": "A scotch and amaretto drink named for the film…" },
    { "name": "Banana Daiquiri", "movie": "The Godfather Part II",  "year": 1974, "note": "Fredo Corleone orders one at a Havana cafe…" },
    { "name": "Godmother",       "movie": "The Godfather Part III", "year": 1990, "note": "Vodka and amaretto, a nod to the films…" }
  ]
}`;
---
<Base
  title="An MCP server for 500 cocktail recipes"
  titleTemplate="%s ~ Cocktail Glass"
  description="A free MCP server for a database of 500 cocktail recipes. Connect any MCP client and search by name, ingredient, or at random — no API key, no sign-up."
  ogImage="/og/for-agents.jpg"
>
  <div class="container agents">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>An AI-readable cocktail database</h1>
      <p class="page-intro">cocktail.glass isn't only 500 recipes for people to read. The whole catalogue is built for machines too. Connect an AI agent over the Model Context Protocol, pull structured JSON, or read any page as Markdown. No API key, no sign-up, no rate limits.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>Connect an AI agent over MCP</h2>
      <p>The fastest way in is the <strong>Model Context Protocol (MCP)</strong> server. It's a remote, stateless endpoint at <code>https://cocktail.glass/mcp</code>. Point any MCP client at it and seven cocktail tools — plus a guided prompt — appear.</p>

      <p class="code-label">One click</p>
      <p class="install-row">
        <a class="install-btn" href={cursorInstall}>Add to Cursor</a>
        <a class="install-btn" href={vscodeInstall}>Add to VS Code</a>
      </p>

      <p class="code-label">Claude Code</p>
      <pre><code>{mcpAddCmd}</code></pre>
      <p class="code-label">Claude Desktop, or any MCP client</p>
      <pre><code>{desktopConfig}</code></pre>
      <p>That's it. No key to paste. The server exposes seven read-only tools — <code>search_cocktails</code>, <code>list_cocktails</code>, <code>get_cocktail_recipe</code>, <code>find_cocktails_by_ingredient</code>, <code>find_cocktails_in_movie</code>, <code>find_makeable_cocktails</code>, and <code>random_cocktail</code> — plus a <code>cocktails_from_my_bar</code> prompt.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>What you can ask it</h2>
      <p>Seven tools and a guided prompt cover the questions that come up around a home bar:</p>
      <ul class="use-cases">
        <li><strong>“What can I make tonight?”</strong> Share the bottles you own — or a photo of your cabinet — and get back the cocktails you can make right now, plus the ones you're a single ingredient short of.</li>
        <li><strong>“How do I make a Last Word?”</strong> A hands-free recipe reference while you're mixing: exact measures, glassware, steps, and garnish.</li>
        <li><strong>“I bought a bottle of mezcal — now what?”</strong> Every cocktail that uses a spirit or liqueur you already own, so nothing gathers dust.</li>
        <li><strong>“Which cocktails turn up in a film?”</strong> Search by movie or TV title and get the drinks featured in it, with a note on each scene.</li>
        <li><strong>“Suggest a few drinks for six guests.”</strong> Build a varied menu across styles, or get one random pick when you can't decide.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>See it work</h2>
      <p>Ask your assistant a question in plain language and it picks the right tool. Here are two real exchanges, end to end:</p>

      <div class="exchange">
        <p class="exchange-step"><span class="exchange-tag exchange-tag--user">You ask</span> “What can I make with Campari?”</p>

        <p class="exchange-step"><span class="exchange-tag">The agent calls a tool</span></p>
        <pre><code>{exampleRequest}</code></pre>

        <p class="exchange-step"><span class="exchange-tag">cocktail.glass returns</span></p>
        <pre><code>{exampleResponse}</code></pre>
        <p class="exchange-note">Four of 29 matches shown. MCP delivers the list as the text content of a standard tool result.</p>

        <p class="exchange-step"><span class="exchange-tag exchange-tag--answer">Your assistant answers</span> “You have 29 options with Campari. The classics are the Negroni and Boulevardier, or a Jungle Bird for something tiki.”</p>
      </div>

      <div class="exchange">
        <p class="exchange-step"><span class="exchange-tag exchange-tag--user">You ask</span> “Which cocktails are in The Godfather?”</p>

        <p class="exchange-step"><span class="exchange-tag">The agent calls a tool</span></p>
        <pre><code>{movieExampleRequest}</code></pre>

        <p class="exchange-step"><span class="exchange-tag">cocktail.glass returns</span></p>
        <pre><code>{movieExampleResponse}</code></pre>
        <p class="exchange-note">Three of six appearances shown. The match runs over the scene description too, so a character, actor, or director — “Hemingway”, “Tarantino” — works as well as a title.</p>

        <p class="exchange-step"><span class="exchange-tag exchange-tag--answer">Your assistant answers</span> “Six across the trilogy — Fredo's banana daiquiri in Part II is the famous one, and the Godfather and Godmother cocktails are named for the films themselves.”</p>
      </div>

      <p>Every result carries a real page URL, so the agent can link straight to the full recipe, with measures, steps, glassware, and garnish.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>More ways in</h2>
      <p>Not every client speaks MCP. The same catalogue is open over plain HTTP:</p>
      <dl class="endpoints">
        <dt><a href="/cocktails.json">/cocktails.json</a></dt>
        <dd>The entire catalogue as one JSON file. All 500 cocktails, with ingredients, measures, and preparation steps.</dd>

        <dt>Markdown content negotiation</dt>
        <dd>Request any page with an <code>Accept: text/markdown</code> header and you get a clean Markdown rendering instead of HTML. It's far cheaper for an LLM to read.</dd>

        <dt><a href="/llms.txt">/llms.txt</a></dt>
        <dd>A structured Markdown map of the whole site, following the llmstxt.org convention.</dd>

        <dt>WebMCP</dt>
        <dd>Agents running inside the browser get the same seven tools in-page through <code>navigator.modelContext</code>, with no connection step.</dd>

        <dt><a href="/.well-known/api-catalog">/.well-known/api-catalog</a> · <a href="/.well-known/mcp/server-card.json">MCP server card</a></dt>
        <dd>Machine-readable discovery documents (RFC 9727 and SEP-2127) so agents and registries can find all of the above on their own.</dd>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <p class="agents-foot">Everything here is read-only and free to use. <a href="/">Browse the recipes →</a></p>
  </div>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .container.agents {
    max-width: 820px;
  }

  .agents .page-header {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .agents h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  }

  .agents .page-intro {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.18rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .agents .card {
    background: var(--glass-bg);
    backdrop-filter: blur(var(--glass-blur));
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(var(--glass-blur));
    border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 2rem 2.25rem;
    box-shadow: var(--glass-shadow);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .agents .card h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .agents .card p {
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .agents .card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .agents a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .agents .code-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.07em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 1.1rem 0 0.4rem;
  }

  .agents .install-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .agents .install-btn {
    background: #2b2420;
    color: #f4e9dd;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 1.15rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s ease;
  }

  .agents .install-btn:hover {
    background: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .agents .use-cases {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .agents .use-cases li {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .agents .use-cases li:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .agents .use-cases strong {
    display: block;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .agents pre {
    background: #2b2420;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  .agents pre code {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #f4e9dd;
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
    white-space: pre;
  }

  .agents code {
    font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.88em;
    background: rgba(60, 40, 30, 0.09);
    padding: 0.12em 0.38em;
    border-radius: 5px;
  }

  .agents .exchange {
    border-left: 3px solid rgba(224, 94, 58, 0.3);
    padding-left: 1.3rem;
    margin: 1.25rem 0;
  }

  .agents .exchange-step {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .agents .exchange-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-right: 0.45rem;
  }

  .agents .exchange-tag--user,
  .agents .exchange-tag--answer {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .agents .exchange-note {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: -0.4rem 0 0.8rem;
  }

  .agents .endpoints {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
  }

  .agents .endpoints dt {
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 1.1rem;
  }

  .agents .endpoints dt:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .agents .endpoints dd {
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .agents-foot {
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 4rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .agents h1 {
      font-size: 2.1rem;
    }

    .agents .card {
      padding: 1.5rem 1.35rem;
    }

    .agents pre code {
      font-size: 0.78rem;
    }
  }
</style>
